I"ß<h2 id="facilities">Facilities</h2>

<p><strong>The Centre is giving new life to an old unitarian church. The main hall has wonderful acoustics and includes a small stage with baby grand piano. The hall can accommodate up to 100 seated people or around 80 seated cabaret style and has a beautiful wooden parquet floor.</strong></p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/hall.jpg" alt="The hall" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>We have a  fully licensed bar with credit card facilities.</li>
  <li>We have tea and coffee making facilities in the foyer with a microwave.</li>
  <li>There are square tables, trestle tables and comfortable chairs.</li>
  <li>We have a <a href="http://lightbox.photo">fully equipped photographic darkroom</a> for processing film and printing photographs, which offers classes and a membership programme.</li>
</ul>

<p>Please note that the building, due to its age and location, is sadly not fully accessible.</p>

<h2 id="hire">Hire</h2>

<p>The building is available for hire for regular events and one-off occasions including childrenâ€™s parties.</p>

<p>Please <a href="hello@westkirbyartscentre.org.uk">contact us</a> for more information on availability and charges.</p>

